name: Nike SB Stefan Janoski “Doernbecher”
description:
The Doernbecher Freestyle 10 collection unveiling continues today with a special Nike SB Zoom Stefan Janoski designed by Ross Hathaway. Hathaway is an avid skater, skier and Tae Kwon Do black belt, all at only eleven years of age. If that wasn't impressive enough, Ross has accomplished all of those feats while battling cystic fibrosis, a chronic disease that affects the lungs and digestive system.

Now Ross will share his story with the world through his special Nike SB Zoom Stefan Janoski design, a model chosen because of his love for skate. “As a skater, I thought a lot about how it would look against the board,” he explained. The shoe's upper features dimensional pops of color inspired by the crystals in his rock collection, while palm trees around the logo reflect his love of tropical locations. A graphical pair of lungs appear beneath the translucent outsoles, while a digital rose appears on the insoles, giving a nod to 65 Roses (a name some kids call cystic fibrosis because it's easier to pronounce).



Read more: http://solecollector.com/news/doernbecher-freestyle-10-nike-sb-zoom-stefan-janoski-by-ross-hathaway/#ixzz2nOtzCMeL

name: Nike Air Jordan 3Lab5
description:
Well, it’s finally here; the Air Jordan 3Lab5 releases tomorrow, September 21, capping off months of hype.

The ultra-premium upper sports luxe leather — entirely covered in black-on-grey Elephant print — with solid black adorning the leather sockliner, laces and midsole. Contrast comes by way of light blue on the branding and forefoot-accent, while a translucent outsole completes the look.

After the initial release of the Air Jordan 9 Johnny Kilroy Pack, it was clear and obvious which colorways were the favorites.  Amongst that list was the “Bentley Ellis” iteration of the Air Jordan 9,  a perfect colorway for a USC or Redskins fan. Lucky for a lot of us, both Finish Line and Nike had a restock, so we decided to grab another pair to check out.
When we polled our audience on their favorite colorway in the collection, the “Bentley Ellis” and “Motorboat Jones” iterations were at the top.  Also known as the “Crawfish” 9s (which is what is scribed on the tongue), the White and Dark Cayenne sneaker is accented with University Gold to give the shoe an added spark.

name: Reebok Question Promo Sample “FOR PLAYER USE ONLY” Pack Size 13 PE LeBron Kobe
description:
Remember when we said the Reebok Question was your favorite player’s favorite shoe? Well it’s true. Just over a decade ago, Kobe Bryant and LeBron James were still the biggest names in basketball. They were also footwear free agents. KB8 took a one-year sneaker sabbatical before inking with the Swoosh and a young King James was still just an amateur. The then-present and future of the game got a hoard of PEs thrown their way with Allen Iverson’s seminal signature being a favorite of both. Fans of the Lakers and LeBron alike pined for both colorways since their first hardwood sighting with no hopes of a proper release. Until now.
The Packer Shoes x Reebok Question “For Player Use Only” Pack sees two of sneakerlore’s most beloved basketball shoes become one of the most random and awesome retro releases to date.

description: After a wildly successful retro of the first colorway of the adidas Originals Mutombo, now the classic model is returning in a new style code. Celebrating the 20th anniversary of Dikembe’s signature sneaker since the 1992-93 season, adidas Originals will release a black/white-purple colorway that pays tribute to the blocking machine’s days with the Denver Nuggets. Using Mutombo’s iconic African patterns and shield logo, along with his 55 jersey number, this edition is composed of nubuck with leather and canvas overlays. A black base is accompanied by white accents and purple detailing.

name: ASICS -  FOTT x Onitsuka Tiger X-Caliber
description:
Russian retailer FOTT has teamed up with Onitsuka Tiger on an exclusive collaboration utilizing the Onitsuka Tiger X-Caliber silhouette as a canvas.

First debuting in 1982, the X-Caliber was revolutionary for its time thanks to the unique midsole and performance credentials, but it’s a shoe that is now seldom seen.

For this collaboration, FOTT has reworked the classic runner’s upper with hardy and weather-resistant Ventile fabric and colored the upper in a combination of blue, green and white that hearkens back to the original store logo. 3M reflective material has been added to the stripes on both sides and the rear panel — a nod to Onitsuka Tiger’s classic California 78 model. A map of Moscow on the insole and FOTT logos on the heel complete the look for this slick collaboration.

name: Concepts x ASICS Gel Lyte III “Three Lies”
description: Boston’s Concepts is honoring a local landmark — the Statue of John Harvard, also known as the Statue of Three Lies — with its upcoming ASICS collaboration. Inspired by the statue’s shoe, and its color in particular, Concepts utilized a plush, premium green suede for the Gel Lyte III‘s upper. Over time statue’s shoe has become a good luck charm and visitors have taken to rubbing the shoe causing the toe box to change color — an attribute that has been mirrored on the collaborative shoe with a gold perforated toe box. The top-notch upper sits atop a speckled grey midsole. The Concepts x ASICS Gel Lyte III will be reaching Concepts soon with other retailers to follow.

Limited Edition Doernbecher Collection shoes will be sold at nike.com and at Nike retail locations across the country beginning Friday, November 30 with all proceeds from sales of the shoes benefitting OHSU Doernbecher. To date, the program has raised more than $4 million.

name: Nike Air Jordan Retro V 5 "Fire Red"
description: It’s been a while since we’ve seen an Air Jordan V drop but for the first time since 2008 a Retro V will hit stores. Originally released in February 1990, the Fire Red Air Jordan V was the first colorway of this model released. Michael Jordan wore the Vs during the majority of the 1989-1990 season in which he won his fourth consecutive scoring title and when he scored his career high 69 points against the Cavs. A black and red midsole complements the all white upper with a fire red inner lining. Taking inspiration from a fighter jet, the 2013 Fire Red V captures the essence of the original but has some unique quirks of its own. The most obvious change from the original is the icy blue bottom on the version that drops today. You’ll also notice the absence of Jordan’s #23 on the outside of the shoe. A reflective 3M tongue remains, as well as the lace clip, mesh overlays, and midsole pattern that are the major characteristics of any V.

name: Nike Air Foamposite Pro – Dr. Doom black / white
description:
*Used - Great Condition!!

The Air Foamposite has been the ‘lone wolf’ of sneaker history. From an outsiders point of view, the Air Foamposite One/Pro was a relatively weird-looking shoe, and with the $170 (and now $220) price-tags, it was merely something to gawk at while browsing around for White-on-White Air Force 1s. Of course, times have changed, and Foams are now the BMOC (big man on campus), so this week’s focus on the Air Foamposite Pro for our Classics Revisited feature has been a refreshing validation for those who were on Foams years before the current mainstream hype. The Air Foamposite always stood alone, but in 2006, Nike Sportswear decided to include it in a special-edition ‘Pack’ or releases known as the Fantastic Four Pack (roughly one year after the the release of the feature film). Which character would it represent? One would guess that a Foamposite would take on the persona of Ben Grimm/Thing considering both share that bulky build, but sadly, the Foamposite stood on its own – again.

description:
*Used - Great Condition

Model:	Air Jordan , Air Jordan 2 (II)
Colorway:	Black / Pro Gold – Lucky Green
Style Code:	318304-071

*Does not come with original box

The Air Jordan 2 (II) Retro – Doernbecher Charity (DB) Black / Pro Gold – Lucky Green was a very interesting shoe, as it has some special cause or reasoning behind it.  They were designed by children, and for that reason it was surprising that they sold so well, selling out online and causing many people to camp out for the store release.  They were designed to help raise money for the Doernbecher Hospital. They feature a black upper wit green designs around the ankle area and toe area.  Many people do not even know that these were ever created, but true Air Jordan fanatics stay on top of their game.

Metallic Silver accents and midsole act in direct contrast to the iced outsole making these shoes very eye-popping. We now know that they will officially release on December 11, 2010

name: Adidas Mutombo
description: This sneaker represented a different time in sneaker culture when it wasn’t a rarity to see a center with  marketable sneakers. After a 20 year hiatus, the original colorway that paid homage to Dikembe’s African heritage with its shield logo dually representing his defensive abilities makes its way back to the forefront with its iconic patterned upper.
